==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Alkaline
<hw>Al"ka*line</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>alcalin</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to an alkali or to
alkalies; having the properties of an alkali.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Alkaline earths</b></col>, <cd>certain substances, as
lime, baryta, strontia, and magnesia, possessing some of the qualities
of alkalies.</cd> -- <col><b>Alkaline metals</b></col>, <cd>potassium,
sodium, c⟦ae⟧sium, lithium, rubidium.</cd> -- <col><b>Alkaline
reaction</b></col>, <cd>a reaction indicating alkalinity, as by the
action on limits, turmeric, etc.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>alkaline-loving</ent>⟦br⟧
